import pandas as pd
import supporter
from keras.models import Sequential
from keras.layers import Dense
from keras.layers import LSTM
from keras.wrappers.scikit_learn import KerasRegressor
from keras.models import load_model
from sklearn.model_selection import GridSearchCV
from sklearn.model_selection import TimeSeriesSplit
from sklearn.model_selection import cross_validate
import joblib
import random
import seaborn as sns
random.seed(7)

#Porcentaje de los datos de entrenamiento
train_size=0.8
#Porcentaje de los datos de Test
test_size=0.2

#Parrilla de hiper-parámetros para GridSearchCV
parameter_space = {
    'epochs': [10,20,50],
    'batch_size' : [10,50,100],
    '_filters': [16, 32],
    '_kernel_size': [1,2,4]
}

"""optimizer = ['SGD', 'Adam']
init_mode = ['glorot_uniform', 'normal', 'uniform']
batch_size = [10, 20, 40, 60, 80, 100]
epochs = [50, 100, 500]
filters = [32, 64]
kernel_sizes = [2,4]"""

#Validación cruzada para series temporales
cv = TimeSeriesSplit(n_splits = 10)
In [2]:
def create_LSTM_model(_optimizer='adam', _init_mode='uniform', _filters=64, _kernel_size=2):
    model = Sequential()
    model.add(LSTM(50, input_shape=(n_predictors, n_features)))
    model.add(Dense(1))
    model.compile(optimizer=_optimizer, loss='mse')
    return model

#Encapsulamos el modelo keras para que sea compatatible con las funciones SkLearn
model_LSTM = KerasRegressor(build_fn=create_LSTM_model, verbose=0)

7 días sin información diaria¶

In [3]:
df_7d_no_info = pd.read_csv(r'./consumo_diario_03_7d_no_info.csv',parse_dates=["Fecha"], index_col=["Fecha"])
In [4]:
X_train_7d_no_info, X_test_7d_no_info, y_train_7d_no_info, y_test_7d_no_info = supporter.split_train_test_deep(df_7d_no_info,
                                                train_size_=train_size,test_size_=test_size,
                                                target="Consumo(t)", _scale=True,verbose=False)

n_predictors = X_train_7d_no_info.shape[1]
n_features = 1
grid = GridSearchCV(estimator=model_LSTM, param_grid=parameter_space, n_jobs=-1, cv=cv) grid_result = grid.fit(X_train_7d_no_info, y_train_7d_no_info) best_conf = grid_result.best_params_ joblib.dump(best_conf, 'LSTM_7d_no_info_normalizado_best_conf.pkl') best_estimator = grid_result.best_estimator_ _7d_no_info_RMSE, _7d_no_info_MSE, _7d_no_info_MAE = supporter.crear_tabla_errores_cv_train_deep(best_estimator, X_train_7d_no_info, y_train_7d_no_info, cv, '7 días sin información diaria') joblib.dump(_7d_no_info_RMSE, 'LSTM_7d_no_info_normalizado_RMSE_training.pkl') joblib.dump(_7d_no_info_MSE, 'LSTM_7d_no_info_normalizado_MSE_training.pkl') joblib.dump(_7d_no_info_MAE, 'LSTM_7d_no_info_normalizado_MAE_training.pkl') predictor = best_estimator.model predictor.save('LSTM_7d_no_info_normalizado_best_model.h5')
